Protection from STIs 
&ldquo;Do you and your partner(s) discuss prevention of STIs and human immunodeficiency virus (HIV)?&rdquo; 
&ldquo;Do you and your partner(s) discuss getting tested?&rdquo; 
For condoms:
&ldquo;What protection methods do you use? In what situations do you use condoms?&rdquo; 
Past history of STIs 
&ldquo;Have you ever been tested for STIs and HIV?&rdquo; 
&ldquo;Have you ever been diagnosed with an STI in the past?&rdquo; 
&ldquo;Have any of your partners had an STI?&rdquo; 
Additional questions for identifying HIV and viral hepatitis risk: 
&ldquo;Have you or any of your partner(s) ever injected drugs?&rdquo; 
&ldquo;Is there anything about your sexual health that you have questions about?&rdquo; 
Pregnancy intention 
&ldquo;Do you think you would like to have (more) children in the future?&rdquo; 
&ldquo;How important is it to you to prevent pregnancy (until then)?&rdquo; 
&ldquo;Are you or your partner using contraception or practicing any form of birth control?&rdquo; 
&ldquo;Would you like to talk about ways to prevent pregnancy?&rdquo; 
